  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We compare two POC-tests (INRario2 and CoaguChek) for the INR with the laboratory. Therefore,
      we take bloodsamples (capillary and venous blood) and put it on the tool. After the
      measuring, a number is shown = INR.

      We develop a Bland-Altman-plot for the correlation between the tool value and the laboratory
      value to illustrate the applicability in the clinical daily routine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
